Translated into English as "witch", and is a spiteful person who operates in secret to harm others.

Derived from two words (thaka - [mix] and muthi - [medicine]). Umthakathi being someone who mixes medicine.

Later came to be used to refer only to negative, harmful uses of medicines derived from plants, animals and minerals.

Abathakathi (plural) use poisons and 'familiar' spirits to carry out harmful deeds.

The verb form of the word, i.e. to perform these acts, is to thakatha.